
itools 0.14.8 (2007/03/19)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.catalog        itools.http             itools.uri
  itools.cms            itools.i18n             itools.vfs
  itools.csv            itools.ical             itools.web
  itools.datatypes      itools.rss              itools.workflow
  itools.gettext        itools.schemas          itools.xhtml
  itools.handlers       itools.stl              itools.xliff
  itools.html           itools.tmx              itools.xml

This is a security release:

 - A serious bug has been fixed in "itools.cms". Before 0.14.8, an
   authenticated user was able to succesfully perform any POST request,
   if specially constructed.

Other bugs fixed:

 - A couple of fixes for the calendar object in "itools.cms".
 - Now the AcceptLanguage header is interpreted as case-insensitive.


Credits:

 - Hervé Cauwelier fixed the calendar bugs;
 - J. David Ibáñez fixed the other bugs;


